窗口打开](https://tomcat.apache.org) - Robust, all-round server for Servlet and JSP.\n- [Apache TomEE在新窗口打开](https://tomee.apache.org) - Tomcat plus Java EE.\n- [Jetty在新窗口打开](https://www.eclipse.org/jetty) - Provides a Web server and javax.servlet container, plus support for HTTP/2, WebSocket, OSGi, JMX, JNDI, JAAS and many other integrations.\n- [nanohttpd在新窗口打开](https://github.com/NanoHttpd/nanohttpd) - Tiny, easily embeddable HTTP server.\n- [WebSphere Liberty在新窗口打开](https://developer.ibm.com/wasdev) - Lightweight, modular server developed by IBM.\n- [WildFly在新窗口打开](http://www.wildfly.org) - Formerly known as JBoss and developed by Red Hat with extensive Java EE support.\n\n## Template Engine\n\n*Tools that substitute expressions in a template.*\n\n- [Handlebars.java在新窗口打开](https://jknack.github.io/handlebars.java) - Logicless and semantic Mustache templates.\n- [Jade4J在新窗口打开](https://github.com/neuland/jade4j) - Implementation of Pug (formerly known as Jade).\n- [Jtwig在新窗口打开](http://jtwig.org) - Modular, configurable and fully tested template engine.\n- [Pebble在新窗口打开](http://www.mitchellbosecke.com/pebble/home) - Inspired by Twig and separates itself with its inheritance feature and its easy-to-read syntax. It ships with built-in autoescaping for security and it includes integrated support for internationalization.\n- [Thymeleaf在新窗口打开](http://www.thymeleaf.org) - Aims to be a substitute for JSP and works for XML files.\n\n## Testing\n\n*Tools that test from model to the view.*\n\n### Asynchronous\n\n*Tools that simplify testing asynchronous services.*\n\n- [Awaitility在新窗口打开](https://github.com/jayway/awaitility) - DSL for synchronizing asynchronous operations.\n- [ConcurrentUnit在新窗口打开](https://github.com/jhalterman/concurrentunit) - Toolkit for testing multi-threaded and asynchronous applications.\n- [GreenMail在新窗口打开](http://www.icegreen.com/greenmail) - In-memory email server for integration testing. Supports SMTP, POP3 and IMAP including SSL.\n- [Hoverfly Java在新窗口打开](https://github.com/SpectoLabs/hoverfly-java) - Native bindings for Hoverfly, a proxy which allows you to simulate HTTP services.\n- [REST Assured在新窗口打开](https://github.com/jayway/rest-assured) - DSL for easy testing of REST/HTTP services.\n\n### BDD\n\n*Testing for the software development process that emerged from TDD and was heavily influenced by DDD and OOAD.*\n\n- [Cucumber在新窗口打开](https://github.com/cucumber/cucumber-jvm) - Provides a way to describe features in a plain language which customers can understand.\n- [Cukes-REST在新窗口打开](https://github.com/ctco/cukes-rest) - A collection of Gherkin steps for REST-service testing using Cucumber.\n- [J8Spec在新窗口打开](https://github.com/j8spec/j8spec) - Follows a Jasmine-like syntax.\n- [JBehave在新窗口打开](http://jbehave.org) - Extensively configurable framework that describes stories.\n- [JGiven在新窗口打开](http://jgiven.org) - Provides a fluent API which allows for simpler composition.\n- [Lamdba Behave在新窗口打开](https://github.com/RichardWarburton/lambda-behave) - Aims to provide a fluent API to write tests in long and descriptive sentences that read like plain English.\n\n### Fixtures\n\n*Everything related to the creation and handling of random data.*\n\n- [Beanmother在新窗口打开](https://github.com/keepcosmos/beanmother) - Sets up beans from YAML fixtures.\n- [Fixture Factory在新窗口打开](https://github.com/six2six/fixture-factory) - Generates fake objects from a template.\n- [JFairy在新窗口打开](https://github.com/Codearte/jfairy) - Fake data generator.\n- [Randomized Testing在新窗口打开](https://github.com/randomizedtesting/randomizedtesting) - JUnit test runner and plugins for running JUnit tests with pseudo-randomness.\n- [Java Faker在新窗口打开](https://github.com/DiUS/java-faker) - A port of Ruby\'s fake data generator.\n\n### Frameworks\n\n*Provide environments to run tests for a specific use case.*\n\n- [ArchUnit在新窗口打开](https://github.com/TNG/ArchUnit) - Test library for specifying and asserting architecture rules.\n- [Apache JMeter在新窗口打开](http://jmeter.apache.org) - Functional testing and performance measurements.\n- [Arquillian在新窗口打开](http://arquillian.org) - Integration and functional testing platform for Java EE containers.\n- [Citrus在新窗口打开](https://citrusframework.org) - Integration testing framework that focuses on both client- and server-side messaging.\n- [Gatling在新窗口打开](https://gatling.io) - Load testing tool designed for ease of use, maintainability and high performance.\n- [JUnit在新窗口打开](http://junit.org) - Common testing framework.\n- [Pact JVM在新窗口打开](https://github.com/DiUS/pact-jvm) - Consumer-driven contract testing.\n- [PIT在新窗口打开](http://pitest.org) - Fast mutation-testing framework for evaluating fault-detection abilities of existing JUnit or TestNG test suites.\n\n### Matchers\n\n*Libraries that provide custom matchers.*\n\n- [AssertJ在新窗口打开](https://joel-costigliola.github.io/assertj) - Fluent assertions that improve readability.\n- [JSONAssert在新窗口打开](http://jsonassert.skyscreamer.org) - Simplifies testing JSON strings.\n- [Truth在新窗口打开](https://github.com/google/truth) - Google\'s assertion and proposition framework.\n\n### Miscellaneous\n\n*Other stuff related to testing.*\n\n- [Mutability Detector在新窗口打开](https://github.com/MutabilityDetector/MutabilityDetector) - Reports whether instances of a given class are immutable.\n- [raml-tester在新窗口打开](https://github.com/nidi3/raml-tester) - Tests if a request/response matches a given RAML definition.\n- [TestContainers在新窗口打开](https://github.com/testcontainers/testcontainers-java) - Provides throwaway instances of common databases, Selenium web browsers, or anything else that can run in a Docker container.\n- [pojo-tester在新窗口打开](http://www.pojo.pl) - Automatically performs tests on basic POJO methods.\n\n### Mocking\n\n*Tools which mock collaborators to help testing single, isolated units.*\n\n- [JMockit在新窗口打开](http://jmockit.github.io) - Integration testing, API mocking and faking, and code coverage.\n- [Mockito在新窗口打开](https://github.com/mockito/mockito) - Mocking framework that lets you write tests with a clean and simple API.\n- [MockServer在新窗口打开](https://www.mock-server.com) - Allows mocking of systems integrated with HTTPS.\n- [Moco在新窗口打开](https://github.com/dreamhead/moco) - Concise web services for stubs and mocks.\n- [PowerMock在新窗口打开](https://github.com/jayway/powermock) - Mocks static methods, constructors, final classes and methods, private methods, and removal of static initializers.\n- [WireMock在新窗口打开](http://wiremock.org) - Stubs and mocks web services.\n\n### Parameterization\n\n*Simplifies the writing of parameterized tests.*\n\n- [Burst在新窗口打开](https://github.com/square/burst) - A unit testing library for varying test data.\n- [junit-dataprovider在新窗口打开](https://github.com/TNG/junit-dataprovider) - A TestNG-like data provider/runner for JUnit.\n- [JUnitParams在新窗口打开](https://pragmatists.github.io/JUnitParams) - Creates readable and maintainable parametrised tests.\n\n## Utility\n\n*Libraries which provide general utility functions.*\n\n- [bucket4j在新窗口打开](https://github.com/vladimir-bukhtoyarov/bucket4j) - Rate limiting library based on token-bucket algorithm.\n- [cactoos在新窗口打开](http://www.cactoos.org) - Collection of object-oriented primitives.\n- [CRaSH在新窗口打开](http://www.crashub.org) - Provides a shell into a JVM that\'s running CRaSH. Used by Spring Boot and others.\n- [Dex在新窗口打开](https://github.com/PatMartin/Dex) - Java/JavaFX tool capable of powerful ETL and data visualization.\n- [Embulk在新窗口打开](http://www.embulk.org) - Bulk data loader that helps data transfer between various databases, storages, file formats, and cloud services.\n- [fswatch在新窗口打开](https://github.com/vorburger/ch.vorburger.fswatch) - Micro library to watch for directory file system changes, simplifying java.nio.file.WatchService\n- [Gephi在新窗口打开](https://github.com/gephi/gephi) - Cross-platform for visualizing and manipulating large graph networks.\n- [Guava在新窗口打开](https://github.com/google/guava) - Collections, caching, primitives support, concurrency libraries, common annotations, string processing, I/O, and more.\n- [JADE在新窗口打开](http://jade.tilab.com) - Framework and environment for building and debugging multi-agent systems.\n- [JavaVerbalExpressions在新窗口打开](https://github.com/VerbalExpressions/JavaVerbalExpressions) - Library that helps with constructing difficult regular expressions.\n- [JGit在新窗口打开](https://eclipse.org/jgit) - A lightweight, pure Java library implementing the Git version control system.\n- [minio-java在新窗口打开](https://github.com/minio/minio-java) - Provides simple APIs to access any Amazon S3-compatible object storage server.\n- [Protégé在新窗口打开](https://protege.stanford.edu) - Provides an ontology editor and a framework to build knowledge-based systems.\n- [Underscore-java在新窗口打开](https://github.com/javadev/underscore-java) - Port of Underscore.js functions.\n\n## Version Managers\n\n*Utilities that help create the development shell environment and switch between different Java versions.*\n\n- [jabba在新窗口打开](https://github.com/shyiko/jabba) - Java Version Manager inspired by nvm. Supports Mac OS X, Linux and Windows.\n- [jenv在新窗口打开](https://github.com/gcuisinier/jenv) - Java Version Manager inspired by rbenv. Can configure globally or per project. Tested on Debian and Mac OS X.\n- [SDKMan在新窗口打开](https://github.com/sdkman/sdkman-cli) - Java Version Manager inspired by RVM and rbenv. Supports UNIX-based platforms and Windows.\n\n## Web Crawling\n\n*Libraries that analyze the content of websites.*\n\n- [Apache Nutch在新窗口打开](https://nutch.apache.org) - Highly extensible, highly scalable web crawler for production environments.\n- [Crawler4j在新窗口打开](https://github.com/yasserg/crawler4j) - Simple and lightweight web crawler.\n- [jsoup在新窗口打开](https://jsoup.org) - Scrapes, parses, manipulates and cleans HTML.\n- [StormCrawler在新窗口打开](http://stormcrawler.net) - SDK for building low-latency and scalable web crawlers.\n- [webmagic在新窗口打开](https://github.com/code4craft/webmagic) - Scalable crawler with downloading, url management, content extraction and persistent.\n\n## Web Frameworks\n\n*Frameworks that handle the communication between the layers of a web application.*\n\n- [Apache Tapestry在新窗口打开](https://tapestry.apache.org) - Component-oriented framework for creating dynamic, robust, highly scalable web applications.\n- [Apache Wicket在新窗口打开](https://wicket.apache.org) - Component-based web application framework similar to Tapestry, with a stateful GUI.\n- [Blade在新窗口打开](https://github.com/biezhi/blade) - Lightweight, modular framework that aims to be elegant and simple.\n- [Bootique在新窗口打开](http://bootique.io) - Minimally opinionated framework for runnable apps.\n- [Firefly在新窗口打开](http://www.fireflysource.com) - Asynchronous framework for rapid development of high-performance web application.\n- [Grails在新窗口打开](https://grails.org) - Groovy framework that provides a highly productive environment by favoring convention over configuration, no XML and support for mixins.\n- [Jooby在新窗口打开](http://jooby.org) - Scalable, fast and modular micro-framework that offers multiple programming models.\n- [Ninja在新窗口打开](http://www.ninjaframework.org) - Full-stack web framework.\n- [Pippo在新窗口打开](http://www.pippo.ro) - Small, highly modularized, Sinatra-like framework.\n- [Play在新窗口打开](https://www.playframework.com) - Built on Akka, it provides predictable and minimal resource consumption (CPU, memory, threads) for highly-scalable applications in Java and Scala.\n- [PrimeFaces在新窗口打开](https://primefaces.org) - JSF framework with both free and commercial/support versions and frontend components.\n- [Ratpack在新窗口打开](https://ratpack.io) - Set of libraries that facilitate fast, efficient, evolvable and well-tested HTTP applications.\n- [Takes在新窗口打开](https://github.com/yegor256/takes) - Opinionated web framework which is built around the concepts of True Object-Oriented Programming and immutability.\n- [Vaadin在新窗口打开](https://vaadin.com/home) - Event-driven framework built on top of GWT. Uses server-side architecture with Ajax on the client side.\n\n# Resources\n\n## Awesome Lists\n\n*Awesome lists related to the Java & JVM ecosystem.*\n\n- [Awesome Gradle Plugins在新窗口打开](https://github.com/ksoichiro/awesome-gradle)\n- [AwesomeJavaFX在新窗口打开](https://github.com/mhrimaz/AwesomeJavaFX)\n- [Awesome JVM在新窗口打开](https://github.com/deephacks/awesome-jvm)\n- [Awesome Microservices在新窗口打开](https://github.com/mfornos/awesome-microservices)\n- [Awesome REST在新窗口打开](https://github.com/marmelab/awesome-rest)\n- [Awesome Selenium在新窗口打开](https://github.com/christian-bromann/awesome-selenium)\n- [ciandcd在新窗口打开](https://github.com/ciandcd/awesome-ciandcd)\n- [Useful Java Links在新窗口打开](https://github.com/Vedenin/useful-java-links)\n\n## Communities\n\n*Active discussions.*\n\n- [r/java在新窗口打开](https://www.reddit.com/r/java) - Subreddit for the Java community.\n- [stackoverflow在新窗口打开](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/java) - Question/answer platform.\n- [VirtualJUG在新窗口打开](https://virtualjug.com) - Virtual Java User Group.\n\n## Frontends\n\n*Websites that provide a frontend for this list. Please note, there won\'t be an official website. We don\'t associate with a particular website and everybody is allowed to create one.*\n\n- [java.libhunt.com在新窗口打开](https://java.libhunt.com)\n\n## Influential Books\n\n*Books that made a big impact and are still worth reading.*\n\n- [Core Java Volume I--Fundamentals在新窗口打开](https://www.amazon.com/Core-Java-I-Fundamentals-10th/dp/0134177304)\n- [Core Java, Volume II--Advanced Features在新窗口打开](https://www.amazon.com/Core-Java-II-Advanced-Features-10th/dp/0134177290)\n- [Effective Java (3rd Edition)在新窗口打开](https://www.amazon.com/Effective-Java-3rd-Joshua-Bloch/dp/0134685997)\n- [Java Concurrency in Practice在新窗口打开](https://www.amazon.com/Java-Concurrency-Practice-Brian-Goetz/dp/0321349601)\n- [Thinking in Java在新窗口打开](https://www.amazon.com/Thinking-Java-Edition-Bruce-Eckel/dp/0131872486)\n\n## Podcasts and Screencasts\n\n*Something to look at or listen to while programming.*\n\n- [Java Off Heap在新窗口打开](http://www.javaoffheap.com)\n- [Marco Behler\'s Screencasts在新窗口打开](https://www.marcobehler.com/series) - Screencasts about modern Java development.\n- [The Java Council在新窗口打开](https://virtualjug.com/podcast)\n- [The Java Posse在新窗口打开](http://www.javaposse.com) - Discontinued as of 02/2015.\n\n## Twitter\n\n*Active accounts to follow. Descriptions from Twitter.*\n\n- [Adam Bien在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/AdamBien) - Freelance author, JavaOne Rockstar speaker, consultant, Java Champion.\n- [Aleksey Shipilëv在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/shipilev) - Performance geek, benchmarking czar, concurrency bug hunter.\n- [Antonio Goncalves在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/agoncal) - Java Champion, JUG Leader, Devoxx France, Java EE 6/7, JCP, Author.\n- [Arun Gupta在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/arungupta) - Java Champion, JavaOne Rockstar, JUG Leader, Devoxx4Kids-er, VP of Developer Advocacy at Couchbase.\n- [Brian Goetz在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/BrianGoetz) - Java Language Architect at Oracle.\n- [Bruno Borges在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/brunoborges) - Product Manager/Java Jock at Oracle.\n- [Chris Richardson在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/crichardson) - Software architect, consultant, and serial entrepreneur, Java Champion, JavaOne Rock Star, *POJOs in Action- author.\n- [Ed Burns在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/edburns) - Consulting Member of the Technical Staff at Oracle.\n- [Eugen Paraschiv在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/baeldung) - Author of the Spring Security Course.\n- [Heinz Kabutz在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/heinzkabutz) - Java Champion, speaker, author of The Java Specialists\' Newsletter, concurrency performance expert.\n- [Holly Cummins在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/holly_cummins) - Technical Lead of IBM London\'s Bluemix Garage, Java Champion, developer, author, JavaOne rockstar.\n- [James Weaver在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/JavaFXpert) - Java/JavaFX/IoT developer, author and speaker.\n- [Java EE在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/Java_EE) - Official Java EE Twitter account.\n- [Java Magazine在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/Oraclejavamag) - Official Java Magazine account.\n- [Java在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/java) - Official Java Twitter account.\n- [Javin Paul在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/javinpaul) - Well-known Java blogger.\n- [Josh Long在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/starbuxman) - Spring Advocate at Pivotal, author of O\'Reilly\'s Cloud Native Java- and Building Microservices with Spring Boot, JavaOne Rock Star.\n- [Lukas Eder在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/lukaseder) - Java Champion, speaker, JUG.ch co-leader, Founder and CEO Data Geekery (jOOQ).\n- [Mario Fusco在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/mariofusco) - RedHatter, JUG coordinator, frequent speaker and author.\n- [Mark Heckler在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/MkHeck) - Pivotal Principal Technologist and Developer Advocate, conference speaker, published author, and Java Champion, focusing on Internet of Things and the cloud.\n- [Mark Reinhold在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/mreinhold) - Chief Architect, Java Platform Group, Oracle.\n- [Markus Eisele在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/myfear) - Java EE evangelist, Red Hat.\n- [Martijn Verburg在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/karianna) - London JUG co-leader, speaker, author, Java Champion and much more.\n- [Martin Thompson在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/mjpt777) - Pasty faced performance gangster.\n- [Monica Beckwith在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/mon_beck) - Performance consultant, JavaOne Rock Star.\n- [OpenJDK在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/OpenJDK) - Official OpenJDK account.\n- [Peter Lawrey在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/PeterLawrey) - Peter Lawrey, Java performance expert.\n- [Randy Shoup在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/randyshoup) - Stitch Fix VP Engineering, speaker, JavaOne Rock Star.\n- [Reza Rahman在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/reza_rahman) - Java EE/GlassFish/WebLogic evangelist, author, speaker, open source hacker.\n- [Simon Maple在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/sjmaple) - Java Champion, VirtualJUG founder, LJC leader, RebelLabs author.\n- [Stephen Colebourne在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/jodastephen) - Java Champion, speaker.\n- [Trisha Gee在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/trisha_gee) - Java Champion and speaker.\n- [Venkat Subramaniam在新窗口打开](https://twitter.com/venkat_s) - Author, University of Houston professor, MicroSoft MVP award recipient, JavaOne Rock Star, Java Champion.\n\n## Websites\n\n*Sites to read.*\n\n- [Google Java Style在新窗口打开](https://google.github.io/styleguide/javaguide.html)\n- [InfoQ在新窗口打开](https://www.infoq.com)\n- [Java Algorithms and Clients在新窗口打开](https://algs4.cs.princeton.edu/code)\n- [Java, SQL, and jOOQ在新窗口打开](https://blog.jooq.org)\n- [Java.net在新窗口打开](https://community.oracle.com/community/java)\n- [Javalobby在新窗口打开](https://dzone.com/java-jdk-development-tutorials-tools-news)\n- [JavaWorld在新窗口打开](https://www.javaworld.com)\n- [JAXenter在新窗口打开](https://jaxenter.com)\n- [RebelLabs在新窗口打开](https://zeroturnaround.com/rebellabs)\n- [The Takipi Blog在新窗口打开](http://blog.takipi.com)\n- [TheServerSide.com在新窗口打开](http://www.theserverside.com)\n- [Vanilla Java在新窗口打开](https://vanilla-java.github.io)\n- [Voxxed在新窗口打开](https://www.voxxed.com)\n\n# Contributing\n\nContributions are very welcome!\n\nPlease have a look at the [CONTRIBUTING在新窗口打开](https://github.com/akullpp/awesome-java/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guidelines.\n\n---\n\n原文链接：https://pdai.tech/md/java/others/java-others-awesome-java.html','https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516116216624-53e697fedbea?w=800','Java其它相关',NULL,0,NULL,'pdai-java-others-java-others-awesome-java','Awesome Java - 技术博客','Frameworks that ease bean mapping. Tools that handle the build cycle and dependencies of an application. Libraries to ma...',0,'PUBLISHED',6508,878,401,27,'2026-04-06 00:00:00','2026-04-06 00:00:00','2026-05-08 22:55:13',NULL,0) ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE `author_id`=VALUES(`author_id`),`title`=VALUES(`title`),`summary`=VALUES(`summary`),`content`=VALUES(`content`),`cover_url`=VALUES(`cover_url`),`category`=VALUES(`category`),`offline_reason`=VA